<recipe 
xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io" 
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd"> 
                                                                                
    <title>Tuna Pasta</title>
    <filename>tuna_pasta.xml</filename>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>



    <part>
        <title>Main</title>
        <ingredient>500gms pasta cooked to packet directions</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1 large can tuna in water drained</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1 bunch parsley chopped </ingredient>
        <ingredient>400 gms cheese grated</ingredient>
        <ingredient>salt and pepper to taste</ingredient>
        <ingredient>One quantity white sauce</ingredient>
        <step>Add all ingredients together, except cheese and stir well. Stir in bowls with good handful of cheese on top.</step>
    </part>


    <part>
        <title>White sauce</title>
        <ingredient>110 gms butter</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/3 cup flour</ingredient>
        <ingredient>500ml milk</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Sand white pepper to taste</ingredient>
        <ingredient>Pinch Grated nutmeg</ingredient>
        
        <step>Melt butter in small saucepan, then add flour stirring until all lumps removed. Add a small amount of milk (about 1/4-1/3 cup) and stir continuously until it thickens. Add more milk as before and continue until all the milk is used up. Add salt and pepper and nutmeg and stir well. Use immediately.</step>
    </part>

</recipe>